scan(string, set) returns the position of the first character
in string that is also in set. It returns 0 if none is found.

string = [ abc123 ] scan(s,set) = 4
string = [ no digits ] scan(s,set) = 0
string = [   leading ] scan(s,set) = 0
string = [ hello, world ] scan(s,set) = 0
string = [ ABCdef ] scan(s,set) = 0
string = [  ] scan(s,set) = 0

different sets:
scan('abc123', '0123456789') = 4
scan('abc123', 'abc')        = 1
scan('abc123', 'xyz')        = 0

back=.true. searches from the right:
scan('abc123abc', 'abc')              = 1
scan('abc123abc', 'abc', back=.true.) = 9

blank is just another character in set:
scan('no digits', ' ') = 3

case-sensitive examples:
scan('ABCdef', 'abc') = 0
scan('ABCdef', 'ABC') = 1
